klomp - CLI music player

FILES
klomp - interactive playlist viewer and editor
klomp-call-handler - watches for calls on the n900 to turn off klomplayer
klomp-cmd - sends messages to mplayer, and modifies playlist
klomp-db - manages and queries a sqlite database. reads tags
klomp-fifo-writer - writes to the mplayer fifo at fixed interval
klomplayer - mplayer wrapper that updates a file with time position
klomp-search - interactive frontend to klomp-db
klomp-term - launches klomp in a gnome-terminal
flacmirror - rsync style ogg->flac conversion util
COPYING - GPLv3
README - ?????? wtf is this thing?


klomp-db handles: mp3, flac, ogg, m4a, wma, wav
everything else relies on mplayer


dependencies:
klomp, klomp-search           perl, Term::ReadKey
klomp-call-handler            python
klomp-cmd, klomp-fifo-writer  perl
klomplayer                    perl, mplayer

klomp-db
 to update the library and read tags from files, you need:
   mp3info and mp3info2 {mp3}
     sudo apt-get install mp3info
   lltag {ogg and flac}
     sudo apt-get install lltag
   perl module Audio::WMA {wma}
     cpan Audio::WMA
   AtomicParsley {mp4, m4a, m4p, m4v, m4b}
     sudo apt-get install atomicparsley
 to get japanese transliteration, you need:
   perl module Lingua::JA::Romanize::Japanese

